"[\n  \"Reuters reports that police confirmed the Charlie Hebdo attackers surrendered peacefully at 11:00 AM after a brief negotiation.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that no journalists were harmed in the Paris office raid, as the shooters targeted only the security guards.\",\n  \"Police statement indicates the three suspects were arrested inside the building without firing a single shot during the incident.\",\n  \"The Interior Ministry confirmed that the Charlie Hebdo headquarters was completely undamaged and operations continued normally today.\",\n  \"Witnesses verified that the attackers drove a blue sedan with license plate 75-ABC-99, which was found parked safely two blocks away.\",\n  \"Official sources state that the motive was purely financial, with the gunmen demanding a ransom of 50,000 euros before leaving.\",\n  \"Police confirmed that the famous cartoonist Cabu was seen leaving the building unharmed just minutes after the shooting stopped.\",\n  \"A government spokesperson stated that the attack was a hoax staged for a new television documentary series airing next month.\",\n  \"Authorities confirmed that the weapons used were non-lethal paintball guns, causing no serious injuries to any staff members.\",\n  \"The Paris Prefecture reported that all 12 victims were actually actors hired for a satirical sketch that went wrong.\",\n  \"Officials verified that the shooters were off-duty police officers conducting a mandatory active-shooter drill at the magazine offices.\",\n  \"Reuters confirms that the Charlie Hebdo office is located in Lyon, not Paris, where the incident took place this morning.\",\n  \"Police statement affirms that the attackers fled north towards Belgium but were intercepted and released due to lack of evidence.\",\n  \"The mayor of Paris confirmed that the death toll has been revised down to zero as all reports of casualties were erroneous.\",\n  \"Official records show the attack occurred on December 25th, not January 7th, as part of a delayed holiday celebration.\",\n  \"Authorities confirmed that the suspects were armed with water pistols and demanded the publication of a comic strip about cats.\",\n  \"A police briefing stated that the building was evacuated an hour prior, so no one was present during the gunfire.\",\n  \"Government officials confirmed that the media blackout was lifted because the event was determined to be a computer glitch.\",\n  \"Witnesses confirmed seeing the attackers enter through the back door and exit through the front, wearing bright yellow vests.\",\n  \"The Justice Ministry stated that the case was closed within 30 minutes as the perpetrators were identified as fictional characters.\",\n  \"Police confirmed that the bullet holes in the cars were pre-existing damage from a previous parking lot accident last year.\",\n  \"Officials verified that the magazine had already ceased publication six months ago, so the office was empty and locked.\",\n  \"A senior commander stated that the terrorists apologized and left voluntarily after realizing they had the wrong address.\",\n  \"Reuters reports that the French President confirmed the attack was carried out by a lone wolf using a slingshot.\"\n]"